<item>
            <title>[LU-10746] SLES12-SP2: Add support to build against GA kernel</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10746</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The SUSE build system for kernel modules uses the GA (&quot;release&quot;) kernel as a base.  This means that the ext4 implementation it uses will grow out-of-date over time.  SUSE has patches that add the -stable ext4 patches to a new ldiskfs/kernel_patches/patches/4.4-stable directory to keep the ext4 implementation used in ldiskfs updated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
